1
00:00:01,520 --> 00:00:06,240
THIS DRAMA IS CREATED
FOR ENTERTAINMENT PURPOSES

2
00:00:06,320 --> 00:00:10,800
ALL CHARACTERS, SETTINGS
AND EVENTS ARE ENTIRELY FICTITIOUS

3
00:00:10,880 --> 00:00:15,920
THERE IS NO INTENT TO REFERENCE
ANY ORGANIZATIONS OR INDIVIDUALS

4
00:03:16,480 --> 00:03:19,480
If you save my life,
I'll hand the Death File over to…

5
00:03:22,160 --> 00:03:23,400
Hey!

6
00:03:23,480 --> 00:03:24,440
I can't, Sarge.

7
00:03:30,640 --> 00:03:31,960
Hey. Moh. You're alive?

8
00:03:32,040 --> 00:03:33,360
I was just about to go help you…

9
00:03:33,440 --> 00:03:34,760
- Moh. Moh.
- Moh!

10
00:03:34,840 --> 00:03:36,440
We followed your lead

11
00:03:36,520 --> 00:03:38,240
because we believed
you'd get us out alive!

12
00:03:39,080 --> 00:03:41,600
<i>This mission is off. I'll do it alone.</i>

13
00:03:42,400 --> 00:03:43,520
<i>You bunch of trash.</i>

14
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:53,440
<i>On the battlefield,</i>
<i>if you don't know how to love yourself,</i>

15
00:03:53,520 --> 00:03:56,360
No one else will love you.
You'll all die anyway.

16
00:03:57,560 --> 00:04:01,080
So all those subordinates who died
died because you were selfish, right?

17
00:04:11,720 --> 00:04:13,160
- Let's go!
- Hey, don't rush in yet!

18
00:04:16,920 --> 00:04:18,120
Are you all right?

19
00:04:18,640 --> 00:04:20,440
Fall back. Get them out. Fall back.

20
00:04:26,880 --> 00:04:27,840
Don't go yet.

21
00:04:32,760 --> 00:04:34,840
Hey! Wake up!

22
00:04:34,920 --> 00:04:36,000
Hey!

23
00:04:37,320 --> 00:04:38,200
Corporal!

24
00:04:50,160 --> 00:04:51,800
The hell are you doing?
This place isn't safe.

25
00:04:53,040 --> 00:04:55,600
I was sitting here just fine,

26
00:04:55,680 --> 00:04:58,560
then you showed up
and now it's not safe anymore.

27
00:05:01,760 --> 00:05:03,920
I think you should calm down.

28
00:05:04,520 --> 00:05:08,760
Let go of me and let's talk
like a normal couple having a fight, okay?

29
00:05:08,840 --> 00:05:09,680
Yeah.

30
00:05:12,840 --> 00:05:14,720
MADE-TO-ORDER FOOD
FRIED FISHBALL

31
00:05:16,400 --> 00:05:17,560
It's nothing.

32
00:05:18,280 --> 00:05:21,960
Just a couple fighting. No action
in the bedroom for me last night, so…

33
00:05:22,040 --> 00:05:25,200
She got a bit rough. Sorry, honey.

34
00:05:25,280 --> 00:05:26,360
Sorry.

35
00:05:29,440 --> 00:05:31,960
You're supposed to be an agent.

36
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:34,840
Learn how to blend in.

37
00:05:34,920 --> 00:05:39,080
Be subtle. Look at you,
dressed like you're going to Siam Paragon.

38
00:05:46,840 --> 00:05:48,760
Make it convincing.

39
00:05:48,840 --> 00:05:52,160
Act like a couple
clearing their relationship issues.

40
00:05:59,960 --> 00:06:01,480
Heavyweight, huh?

41
00:06:03,840 --> 00:06:05,640
I know what happened to your team.

42
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:10,320
What kind of team leader
breaks his own team?

43
00:06:20,760 --> 00:06:22,520
You're gonna get drunk and talk nonsense.

44
00:06:26,520 --> 00:06:27,920
I've studied your background.

45
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:30,000
I know what happened in the past.

46
00:06:31,160 --> 00:06:33,600
You blame yourself
for getting your men killed,

47
00:06:33,680 --> 00:06:37,200
but you actually tried
to protect them then and now.

48
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:42,720
Because you know that after this,

49
00:06:42,800 --> 00:06:45,080
Tiangmon will hit back harder,

50
00:06:45,160 --> 00:06:47,640
so you pushed everyone away

51
00:06:47,720 --> 00:06:49,240
before more people died.

52
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:54,840
Oh.

53
00:06:54,920 --> 00:06:58,240
I'm not a saint. I just want to go solo.

54
00:07:00,320 --> 00:07:02,320
Work alone, get paid alone.

55
00:07:02,400 --> 00:07:05,640
Why rely on the Seven Legends?
I can handle it and get rich on my own.

56
00:07:12,280 --> 00:07:13,160
Hey!

57
00:07:14,760 --> 00:07:17,040
Is it cracked? That's a glass!

58
00:07:17,640 --> 00:07:19,360
It's just a bump. It was just the edge

59
00:07:19,440 --> 00:07:20,920
of the glass.

60
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:27,920
Hey, please respect my head.
Do you still see me as a human?

61
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:30,400
It's because you're being stubborn,
refusing the truth.

62
00:07:35,400 --> 00:07:36,600
Auntie, another bottle, please.

63
00:07:37,280 --> 00:07:38,120
Huh?

64
00:07:40,120 --> 00:07:41,280
That was fast.

65
00:07:49,280 --> 00:07:51,800
If you want me to like you,
stop acting like a dog.

66
00:07:51,880 --> 00:07:53,800
If I wanted a dog,
I'd pick one up anywhere.

67
00:07:56,880 --> 00:07:58,360
Prove yourself

68
00:07:59,200 --> 00:08:00,840
that you're worthy of me.

69
00:08:04,480 --> 00:08:05,440
So,

70
00:08:06,560 --> 00:08:10,000
if I finish this bottle and still stand,

71
00:08:10,080 --> 00:08:12,440
you go back to work with everyone.

72
00:08:12,520 --> 00:08:15,560
Be the leader
people want to work with. Okay?

73
00:08:19,920 --> 00:08:21,960
Hey, easy, easy.

74
00:08:30,760 --> 00:08:32,360
Sarge.

75
00:08:32,440 --> 00:08:33,480
Not done yet.

76
00:08:40,159 --> 00:08:43,840
Look at me. I'm not drunk.

77
00:08:44,760 --> 00:08:47,080
Yeah, great. Good job.

78
00:08:47,160 --> 00:08:49,480
- Hey, hey. Whoa.
- Hey.

79
00:08:49,560 --> 00:08:51,320
You can just go.

80
00:08:51,400 --> 00:08:53,240
- Hey.
- I'm lying here.

81
00:08:53,320 --> 00:08:56,200
Sarge, you can't sit here. Get up.

82
00:08:56,280 --> 00:08:57,960
I'm not sitting. I'm lying.

83
00:08:58,040 --> 00:09:00,080
- Lie what? Get up.
- I'm lying. Leave me alone!

84
00:09:00,160 --> 00:09:02,240
- Get up.
- Let go of me.

85
00:09:02,320 --> 00:09:03,960
- You a naggy wife or something?
- Come.

86
00:09:04,040 --> 00:09:06,080
- Let go. Let go of me.
- Whoa.

87
00:09:06,160 --> 00:09:10,160
I'm the Sarge.

88
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:13,480
I can take care of myself.

89
00:09:13,560 --> 00:09:15,240
- Go wherever you want!
- Yeah, go!

90
00:09:15,320 --> 00:09:16,920
Go! Go!

91
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:18,280
- Go!
- Go!

92
00:09:19,840 --> 00:09:21,560
Go! I'm lying here.

93
00:09:22,920 --> 00:09:23,880
So soft.

94
00:09:25,800 --> 00:09:28,800
Hey, Sarge! you can't sleep there!

95
00:09:34,640 --> 00:09:36,960
Get up.

96
00:09:37,040 --> 00:09:38,760
- Yeah, hit me more.
- Sarge.

97
00:09:40,880 --> 00:09:41,960
Sarge…

98
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:44,800
Get up.

99
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:50,440
Sarge!

100
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:03,920
Tonight,

101
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:06,560
just stay here, Sarge.

102
00:10:16,920 --> 00:10:18,280
Your shirt reeks.

103
00:10:20,360 --> 00:10:23,440
- Take it off.
- Hey, I surrender.

104
00:10:25,080 --> 00:10:26,200
You're right.

105
00:10:27,560 --> 00:10:29,120
I won't let

106
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:31,640
my men die in front of me again.

107
00:10:32,520 --> 00:10:34,000
If the mission fails,

108
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:36,760
I take responsibility alone.

109
00:10:36,840 --> 00:10:38,840
It has to be me. My men must not die.

110
00:10:38,920 --> 00:10:41,400
No one dies again. No one!

111
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:45,040
Thought you were about to lose it.
I'd hit back.

112
00:10:59,160 --> 00:11:00,400
That's it.

113
00:11:03,480 --> 00:11:05,960
With a face like that,

114
00:11:06,960 --> 00:11:09,920
if you'd stop acting like a jerk,

115
00:11:11,880 --> 00:11:14,960
you'd steal my heart already.

116
00:11:29,320 --> 00:11:31,880
You know, when I was a kid,
I was even wilder.

117
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:36,800
And my dad liked that.

118
00:11:37,960 --> 00:11:40,600
One day my mom told me

119
00:11:40,680 --> 00:11:44,200
Dad's boss invested in a hotel

120
00:11:44,280 --> 00:11:46,480
for him to develop.

121
00:11:46,560 --> 00:11:49,640
Oh, I was so happy.

122
00:11:49,720 --> 00:11:53,280
I asked him every day to take me there.

123
00:11:56,440 --> 00:11:59,160
I wanted to be an adventurer.

124
00:11:59,240 --> 00:12:01,200
- An adventurer?
- Yeah.

125
00:12:16,240 --> 00:12:18,120
Hey. Whoa.

126
00:12:47,320 --> 00:12:48,440
What a relief.

127
00:12:49,600 --> 00:12:50,840
Good thing it didn't happen.

128
00:12:52,640 --> 00:12:54,040
No wonder

129
00:12:54,120 --> 00:12:57,120
the doctor warned us not to get drunk,

130
00:12:57,200 --> 00:12:58,280
or else…

131
00:12:58,360 --> 00:13:00,320
Oh, damn.

132
00:13:21,160 --> 00:13:23,240
Hello, yes, Dan?

133
00:13:23,320 --> 00:13:25,520
<i>My mission's complete, Ms. Duangnet.</i>

134
00:13:25,600 --> 00:13:28,200
I know where Tiangmon's

135
00:13:28,280 --> 00:13:30,800
online gambling
and call center scam base is.

136
00:13:32,080 --> 00:13:36,000
Good job, Dan. I know where Sarge is.

137
00:13:36,080 --> 00:13:37,440
I'll send the location.

138
00:13:37,520 --> 00:13:39,080
Take him to the safe house
for the briefing.

139
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:46,960
Love hotel?

140
00:13:47,480 --> 00:13:48,720
The hell is Sarge doing there?

141
00:14:26,880 --> 00:14:29,240
- Sarge, walk straight. Whoa.
- Hey, Dan.

142
00:14:29,320 --> 00:14:32,080
- Don't puke, don't puke! Hold it!
- Hold it, Sarge!

143
00:14:32,160 --> 00:14:33,680
Don't puke. No.

144
00:14:45,760 --> 00:14:48,480
What's wrong with him?

145
00:14:48,560 --> 00:14:50,480
Why is he like this?

146
00:14:52,320 --> 00:14:55,920
I don't know. He's totally hungover
and talking nonsense.

147
00:14:57,880 --> 00:14:58,960
He must've been wasted.

148
00:15:01,480 --> 00:15:03,560
But the resort staff said

149
00:15:03,640 --> 00:15:06,920
Sarge checked in with a woman.

150
00:15:08,160 --> 00:15:11,120
When they described her, I freaked out.

151
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:15,280
It sounded exactly like you, Ms. Duangnet.

152
00:15:16,440 --> 00:15:20,080
That's crazy. Me?
Going to a resort with him?

153
00:15:20,160 --> 00:15:21,600
- I remember now.
- Huh?

154
00:15:24,720 --> 00:15:27,080
I was eating <i>larb</i>,

155
00:15:28,480 --> 00:15:30,160
and then…

156
00:15:34,360 --> 00:15:35,840
someone smashed a glass on my head.

157
00:15:38,160 --> 00:15:39,440
- I got even drunker.
- Huh?

158
00:15:41,200 --> 00:15:42,200
Then I blacked out.

159
00:15:43,640 --> 00:15:46,040
So you don't remember
taking a woman to the resort?

160
00:15:46,120 --> 00:15:47,720
I took a woman?

161
00:15:48,560 --> 00:15:49,680
Why don't I remember?

162
00:15:50,400 --> 00:15:51,400
Damn, what a waste.

163
00:15:52,640 --> 00:15:53,600
Enough.

164
00:15:54,600 --> 00:15:55,880
The mission matters more.

165
00:15:55,960 --> 00:15:59,160
Getting wasted like this

166
00:15:59,760 --> 00:16:01,960
risks exposing secrets.

167
00:16:02,040 --> 00:16:04,920
I'll discipline him myself. Go.

168
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:06,040
Let's go, Sarge.

169
00:16:06,120 --> 00:16:07,200
- Okay.
- Hold it in, Sarge.

170
00:16:07,280 --> 00:16:08,640
Go get punished.

171
00:16:08,720 --> 00:16:10,800
- Punished, punished.
- Go.

172
00:16:10,880 --> 00:16:13,520
Lucky you blacked out.

173
00:16:15,400 --> 00:16:17,360
Who said I don't remember, honey?

174
00:16:20,080 --> 00:16:21,560
I'm about to puke for real.

175
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:23,440
I helped you.

176
00:16:24,400 --> 00:16:27,120
Shut up and don't tell anyone.

177
00:16:30,240 --> 00:16:31,200
The plan

178
00:16:31,920 --> 00:16:35,360
to wipe out Tiangmon's online
gambling and call center scam network.

179
00:16:36,200 --> 00:16:37,040
This is the place.

180
00:16:37,120 --> 00:16:38,720
Dan, are you sure

181
00:16:38,800 --> 00:16:40,600
Tiangmon's daughter isn't fooling you

182
00:16:40,680 --> 00:16:44,200
and luring us into a trap to kill us all?

183
00:16:44,280 --> 00:16:45,960
No, Sarge.

184
00:16:46,640 --> 00:16:50,320
I spent time with her.
I know what kind of person she is.

185
00:16:50,400 --> 00:16:51,520
She's a good person.

186
00:16:52,080 --> 00:16:54,880
Just unlucky to be Tiangmon's daughter.

187
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:59,840
I think you're blinded
by her looks, her rich charm,

188
00:16:59,920 --> 00:17:01,440
and you believe everything she says.

189
00:17:02,160 --> 00:17:03,160
Moh.

190
00:17:03,240 --> 00:17:07,000
That mouth of yours
is why Sarge beat you up.

191
00:17:07,079 --> 00:17:10,400
If you don't know, shut up.
I'm not joking with you idiots.

192
00:17:11,640 --> 00:17:14,640
Open your eyes.
Sarge stabbed me in the back.

193
00:17:14,720 --> 00:17:15,839
Or were you just an idiot?

194
00:17:15,920 --> 00:17:17,440
- You left me like that.
- Moh.

195
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:20,920
- Stop!
- Talk nicely.

196
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:22,440
- Stop!
- Yes.

197
00:17:27,800 --> 00:17:28,960
Sit.

198
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:35,880
No wonder people looked down on you
and fired you.

199
00:17:36,920 --> 00:17:38,640
Low patience, selfish.

200
00:17:38,720 --> 00:17:40,720
You said you wanted a second chance.

201
00:17:40,800 --> 00:17:43,240
Just a lie to look cool.
You don't care about the country.

202
00:17:45,160 --> 00:17:46,280
Bunch of trash.

203
00:17:49,640 --> 00:17:50,640
Khim. Napa.

204
00:17:57,040 --> 00:17:59,280
You've been undercover
in Pha Mok for a long time.

205
00:17:59,360 --> 00:18:02,680
Beyond Tiangmon's gambling site
and call center scam network

206
00:18:02,760 --> 00:18:04,840
that stole from countless innocents,

207
00:18:05,720 --> 00:18:07,400
is there something worse than that?

208
00:18:08,080 --> 00:18:11,400
If you think Natee's
human-trafficking ring was bad,

209
00:18:14,400 --> 00:18:16,720
what Napa and I faced…

210
00:18:17,360 --> 00:18:18,880
They were ruthless.

211
00:18:20,600 --> 00:18:22,520
Calling them monsters is too kind.

212
00:18:24,240 --> 00:18:26,520
<i>Those images still haunt us.</i>

213
00:18:26,600 --> 00:18:29,040
<i>The day I came looking for my sister here…</i>

214
00:18:29,120 --> 00:18:30,200
Hey, where are you going?

215
00:18:30,280 --> 00:18:33,680
<i>We discovered how they deal</i>
<i>with slave-labor victims</i>

216
00:18:34,480 --> 00:18:36,000
<i>who were forced to scam</i>

217
00:18:37,440 --> 00:18:40,520
<i>and tried to escape this hell.</i>

218
00:18:44,800 --> 00:18:46,960
That's what they do to innocent people.

219
00:18:47,040 --> 00:18:49,960
Some know and still work as scammers,

220
00:18:50,720 --> 00:18:52,080
but many

221
00:18:52,160 --> 00:18:55,760
were tricked into coming here
and are waiting for help.

222
00:18:55,840 --> 00:18:58,240
Maybe some people we know

223
00:18:58,320 --> 00:19:01,520
are their victims.

224
00:19:03,440 --> 00:19:06,200
Even without a useless team
like the Seven Legends,

225
00:19:07,240 --> 00:19:09,280
I'll wipe out this network myself.

226
00:19:50,280 --> 00:19:51,400
Mr. Dan?

227
00:19:56,400 --> 00:19:57,240
Mr. Dan.

228
00:19:58,040 --> 00:19:59,080
Mr. Dan.

229
00:20:03,840 --> 00:20:05,280
Where did he go?

230
00:20:06,520 --> 00:20:07,440
Mr. Dan.

231
00:20:10,200 --> 00:20:11,160
Mr. Dan.

232
00:20:15,640 --> 00:20:16,520
Dad?

233
00:20:17,040 --> 00:20:18,880
You're making me worried again.

234
00:20:20,920 --> 00:20:23,520
Why worry? I'm fine.

235
00:20:23,600 --> 00:20:26,000
You're gone all night.
How could I not worry?

236
00:20:30,040 --> 00:20:32,920
Here. That guy from the hospital,

237
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:34,720
I had my men check his background.

238
00:20:35,360 --> 00:20:37,560
Nothing about him is real. Look.

239
00:20:38,840 --> 00:20:42,280
Dad, you have no right
to do this to my friend.

240
00:20:44,040 --> 00:20:45,240
He's not your friend.

241
00:20:46,160 --> 00:20:48,880
He's using you to get our secrets.

242
00:20:50,480 --> 00:20:53,640
Arab. Arab, let my daughter go.

243
00:20:59,160 --> 00:21:02,320
Listen. I'm not mad at you

244
00:21:02,400 --> 00:21:04,080
that he took you here and there.

245
00:21:04,160 --> 00:21:06,440
Just tell me where he is.

246
00:21:06,520 --> 00:21:08,320
I don't know.

247
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:11,320
He just helped me and brought me here.

248
00:21:11,400 --> 00:21:14,400
Is it wrong that I feel
safer with him than with you?

249
00:21:14,480 --> 00:21:15,960
What did you tell him?

250
00:21:19,200 --> 00:21:22,360
I didn't tell him anything.
Just small talk.

251
00:21:22,440 --> 00:21:26,360
Do you understand? These people
are destroying my life! Do you?!

252
00:21:26,440 --> 00:21:27,760
Dad.

253
00:21:28,480 --> 00:21:30,040
I told you

254
00:21:30,120 --> 00:21:32,240
I didn't say anything about your work.

255
00:21:33,400 --> 00:21:35,800
- Take Mook to the car.
- Dad!

256
00:21:35,880 --> 00:21:36,920
Get in the car!

257
00:21:38,200 --> 00:21:39,280
Please, Ms. Mook.

258
00:21:42,400 --> 00:21:45,640
If she weren't your daughter,
I'd already have my answer.

259
00:21:45,720 --> 00:21:48,760
Arab, stay away from my daughter.

260
00:21:48,840 --> 00:21:50,160
Because of your daughter,

261
00:21:51,040 --> 00:21:52,400
everything could collapse.

262
00:21:53,760 --> 00:21:56,360
If your network falls like Natee's,

263
00:21:57,280 --> 00:21:59,840
even as Boss's right-hand man,
that started it all with him,

264
00:22:01,040 --> 00:22:02,320
you won't be spared.

265
00:22:04,160 --> 00:22:06,920
Listen, I know

266
00:22:07,000 --> 00:22:09,520
that Pha Mok is boss's all-in gamble.

267
00:22:10,360 --> 00:22:13,520
But Mook is my daughter. I know her.

268
00:22:13,600 --> 00:22:15,320
Follow my plan.

269
00:22:15,400 --> 00:22:16,560
She'll help us.

270
00:22:20,880 --> 00:22:23,440
Okay. That sounds interesting.

271
00:22:24,960 --> 00:22:26,440
But there's one more person
I need to check.

272
00:22:26,520 --> 00:22:27,520
Stop.

273
00:22:28,040 --> 00:22:30,640
If it's who I think,
I'll handle it myself.

274
00:22:41,160 --> 00:22:42,360
How are you guys feeling?

275
00:22:43,400 --> 00:22:45,400
Got wrecked by a woman, huh?

276
00:22:47,120 --> 00:22:48,400
Lost face?

277
00:22:48,480 --> 00:22:49,920
Isn't that because of you, Sarge?

278
00:22:51,800 --> 00:22:54,640
- Not over yet, Moh?
- Hey enough already.

279
00:22:54,720 --> 00:22:55,760
- Easy, bro.
- Moh.

280
00:22:55,840 --> 00:22:57,720
- Enough.
- Don't stop them.

281
00:22:57,800 --> 00:22:59,400
Fight. Just fight.

282
00:22:59,480 --> 00:23:01,040
Fight. I wanna see it.

283
00:23:01,120 --> 00:23:03,840
I've played around with women,
been cursed at plenty,

284
00:23:03,920 --> 00:23:07,440
but never felt this humiliated.

285
00:23:07,520 --> 00:23:09,840
If you're gonna fight, do it.
I wanna see it.

286
00:23:09,920 --> 00:23:10,880
- Fight.
- Yeah.

287
00:23:10,960 --> 00:23:12,680
- Go ahead.
- As for me, if I die,

288
00:23:12,760 --> 00:23:15,000
I'll die a legend in the battlefield.

289
00:23:17,440 --> 00:23:19,480
- What the hell are you saying?
- What?

290
00:23:19,560 --> 00:23:21,200
He's just someone nobody understands.

291
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:24,600
But if even one friend here understands,

292
00:23:25,840 --> 00:23:27,400
he'll see his own worth.

293
00:23:31,520 --> 00:23:32,360
Dan.

294
00:23:34,440 --> 00:23:36,200
I'm really sorry about Mookda.

295
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:39,840
I'll try to tone down my craziness

296
00:23:41,120 --> 00:23:43,440
and take advice,
no matter how harsh, fellow warrior.

297
00:23:45,560 --> 00:23:47,440
Still. You're still crazy.

298
00:23:47,520 --> 00:23:49,200
Like the monks say,

299
00:23:49,920 --> 00:23:53,480
when people are united,
the country stands.

300
00:23:54,280 --> 00:23:57,840
When they fall apart,
they destroy themselves without enemies.

301
00:23:57,920 --> 00:24:00,760
Damn. Sadhu.

302
00:24:04,280 --> 00:24:06,560
- Sarge.
- What now, Sarge? Still not over?

303
00:24:24,320 --> 00:24:26,400
If you think I let you risk your life,

304
00:24:27,320 --> 00:24:30,280
abandoned you, didn't back you up,

305
00:24:32,360 --> 00:24:35,280
if you think I'm a leader
who made you lose faith in me,

306
00:24:37,240 --> 00:24:38,240
then take it out on me.

307
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:40,200
‪-Hey, Moh.
‪-Moh.

308
00:24:40,280 --> 00:24:41,320
- Moh, calm down.
- Moh.

309
00:24:41,400 --> 00:24:42,240
Go on.

310
00:24:44,600 --> 00:24:46,320
I once let you risk your life.

311
00:24:49,680 --> 00:24:51,760
This time, I'll put my life in your hands.

312
00:25:13,080 --> 00:25:14,520
I'm not going soft, Sarge.

313
00:25:15,520 --> 00:25:17,600
But I still want you to lead the team.

314
00:25:25,280 --> 00:25:28,560
Sergeant Dab is pretty badass,
Ms. Duangnet.

315
00:25:36,840 --> 00:25:37,840
Not the gun.

316
00:25:43,520 --> 00:25:44,640
You really don't know?

317
00:25:44,720 --> 00:25:45,960
- What's with you?
- Your hand.

318
00:26:04,520 --> 00:26:06,040
PANTONG

319
00:26:08,680 --> 00:26:11,360
<i>The plan to destroy</i>
<i>the second pillar is confirmed, Dad.</i>

320
00:26:11,440 --> 00:26:15,200
<i>Soon, the Seven Legends</i>
<i>will be ready to wipe this base out.</i>

321
00:26:15,280 --> 00:26:17,440
<i>Once this network is gone,</i>

322
00:26:17,520 --> 00:26:19,360
<i>Phoenix will have to show himself.</i>

323
00:26:27,720 --> 00:26:28,800
Come out.

324
00:26:29,480 --> 00:26:31,160
Why are you coming in? I'm not done yet.

325
00:26:31,240 --> 00:26:34,240
Get out! I said get out!

326
00:26:42,400 --> 00:26:44,920
The hell are you doing?
Why are you in the women's restroom?

327
00:26:52,640 --> 00:26:54,280
I let him in.

328
00:26:58,400 --> 00:27:00,080
May I have your phone?

329
00:27:06,120 --> 00:27:07,000
Unlock it for me too.

330
00:27:16,360 --> 00:27:20,160
So you suspect I'm a mole?

331
00:27:24,400 --> 00:27:26,240
- Get out.
- Yes, sir.

332
00:27:32,840 --> 00:27:36,000
Arab said that my daughter's kidnapping

333
00:27:36,640 --> 00:27:37,920
was staged.

334
00:27:39,040 --> 00:27:40,960
But I almost died too.

335
00:27:41,040 --> 00:27:44,520
Exactly. Natee's network got wiped out,

336
00:27:45,360 --> 00:27:46,840
yet you survived.

337
00:27:47,360 --> 00:27:49,080
Of course Arab's suspicious.

338
00:27:54,240 --> 00:27:55,920
Right now, everyone under suspicion

339
00:27:56,000 --> 00:27:57,840
is being investigated.

340
00:27:58,480 --> 00:28:01,240
I saw how Arab interrogated Beauty.

341
00:28:02,920 --> 00:28:05,000
I won't let that happen to you.

342
00:28:06,000 --> 00:28:07,880
That's why I came myself.

343
00:28:14,400 --> 00:28:16,640
You know how I feel about you.

344
00:28:18,360 --> 00:28:19,480
Don't worry.

345
00:28:20,440 --> 00:28:22,920
If I ever find out you betrayed me,

346
00:28:24,040 --> 00:28:25,360
I swear

347
00:28:26,520 --> 00:28:28,480
I'll make you suffer

348
00:28:28,560 --> 00:28:31,120
a hundred times worse

349
00:28:32,080 --> 00:28:34,000
than what Arab did to Beauty.

350
00:28:37,320 --> 00:28:39,120
Before you let me help,

351
00:28:40,000 --> 00:28:41,920
you already checked me thoroughly.

352
00:28:45,280 --> 00:28:48,120
Yes, I trust you.

353
00:28:49,480 --> 00:28:52,920
But I need to prove myself to Boss first.

354
00:28:58,040 --> 00:28:59,560
You'll have to be detained.

355
00:29:01,800 --> 00:29:03,760
And when I find those guys,

356
00:29:05,280 --> 00:29:07,560
shoot them in front of me.

357
00:29:08,600 --> 00:29:10,480
I want to see your loyalty.

358
00:29:14,680 --> 00:29:15,720
Come in.

359
00:29:23,840 --> 00:29:24,920
Take Ms. Ratee.

360
00:29:27,680 --> 00:29:28,680
Please.

361
00:29:41,920 --> 00:29:45,000
Here. I scouted the place.

362
00:29:45,080 --> 00:29:47,960
There are patrols everywhere,
all the time.

363
00:29:48,040 --> 00:29:50,240
This mission's gonna be tough.

364
00:29:52,120 --> 00:29:54,440
They're using
an abandoned hotel as a base.

365
00:29:55,240 --> 00:29:58,280
The security's tight. No one can get in.

366
00:29:59,320 --> 00:30:02,360
A true golden goose for Phoenix.

367
00:30:04,080 --> 00:30:05,320
Seriously,

368
00:30:06,240 --> 00:30:07,560
you wear Khun Phaen charm or what?

369
00:30:07,640 --> 00:30:12,120
How did you get Tiangmon's daughter
to fall for you and spill intel?

370
00:30:12,200 --> 00:30:14,000
I'm not wearing any amulet.

371
00:30:14,080 --> 00:30:16,240
She never told me outright either.

372
00:30:17,160 --> 00:30:19,080
I just felt sorry for her,

373
00:30:19,960 --> 00:30:23,200
and felt for her
for having a father like Tiangmon.

374
00:30:26,720 --> 00:30:28,760
Everything changed

375
00:30:29,400 --> 00:30:31,160
when my mom got sick.

376
00:30:32,680 --> 00:30:34,360
My dad's boss

377
00:30:34,920 --> 00:30:38,240
pressured him to make more money.

378
00:30:40,360 --> 00:30:42,160
After that,

379
00:30:42,240 --> 00:30:44,680
Dad and Mom fought a lot.

380
00:30:46,600 --> 00:30:49,160
Dad became someone else entirely.

381
00:30:54,640 --> 00:30:58,040
If that place held good memories
for you and him,

382
00:30:58,120 --> 00:30:59,840
why not ask him to go back there?

383
00:31:02,000 --> 00:31:03,560
I tried.

384
00:31:04,480 --> 00:31:06,800
But he sealed that place off completely.

385
00:31:06,880 --> 00:31:08,920
No one was allowed anywhere near it.

386
00:31:10,840 --> 00:31:13,520
Sealed it off? Why?

387
00:31:15,280 --> 00:31:18,440
He said there was an accident,

388
00:31:18,520 --> 00:31:20,160
so it became an abandoned hotel.

389
00:31:20,240 --> 00:31:22,160
After that, he shut it down completely.

390
00:31:22,240 --> 00:31:24,000
And no one was allowed near it.

391
00:31:26,120 --> 00:31:27,080
I see.

392
00:31:32,880 --> 00:31:35,200
That's all I know.

393
00:31:35,280 --> 00:31:37,000
So I checked it myself,

394
00:31:37,080 --> 00:31:38,840
and boom.

395
00:31:39,880 --> 00:31:42,200
Just like I thought. Yeah.

396
00:31:43,080 --> 00:31:44,680
This time, I've got a bad feeling.

397
00:31:46,400 --> 00:31:49,080
I can't go with you.
You'll have to handle it yourselves.

398
00:31:50,520 --> 00:31:52,920
Don't worry. Stick to the plan.

399
00:31:53,000 --> 00:31:55,040
Dan, Juk, cut the system

400
00:31:55,120 --> 00:31:56,920
- and prep the bombs.
- Yes, Sarge.

401
00:31:57,000 --> 00:31:59,360
Kla, Tangkuay, go undercover
and secure an escape route.

402
00:31:59,440 --> 00:32:00,280
Yes, Sarge.

403
00:32:00,360 --> 00:32:02,840
Akki, Moh, do what you do best.

404
00:32:02,920 --> 00:32:05,760
Get close,
hack the system, release the virus.

405
00:32:05,840 --> 00:32:06,800
- Yes, Sarge.
- Yes, Sarge.

406
00:32:06,880 --> 00:32:08,000
Uh, wait, Sarge.

407
00:32:08,080 --> 00:32:11,360
So how are Moh and I getting in?

408
00:32:27,120 --> 00:32:28,840
Kla, your cloth.

409
00:32:29,800 --> 00:32:31,360
Your cloth, not your mouth. Hurry.

410
00:32:31,440 --> 00:32:32,440
Yeah.

411
00:32:35,040 --> 00:32:35,920
Uh.

412
00:32:39,240 --> 00:32:42,160
Come on, move. Walk faster.

413
00:32:46,600 --> 00:32:47,880
Stop complaining. Move.

414
00:32:48,680 --> 00:32:50,000
Come on. Don't complain.

415
00:32:54,200 --> 00:32:55,120
Hurry.

416
00:32:56,960 --> 00:32:57,840
Sit here.

417
00:32:59,080 --> 00:33:00,000
Sit down.

418
00:33:02,440 --> 00:33:05,240
Please, I want to go home.
I don't want this job anymore.

419
00:33:05,320 --> 00:33:07,560
Please let me go.
I won't tell anyone. Please.

420
00:33:07,640 --> 00:33:08,920
You won't tell anyone?

421
00:33:09,000 --> 00:33:11,600
- You won't tell anyone, huh?
- Hey!

422
00:33:11,680 --> 00:33:13,440
From now on, you follow every order.

423
00:33:14,480 --> 00:33:17,000
If you hit your target,
you eat and sleep well.

424
00:33:17,800 --> 00:33:21,000
If you miss it,
or ask for help and try to run,

425
00:33:21,080 --> 00:33:22,080
this is what happens.

426
00:33:26,600 --> 00:33:28,400
Damn, they really are brutal.

427
00:33:28,480 --> 00:33:30,720
Think Moh and Akki will make it?

428
00:33:30,800 --> 00:33:31,640
No idea.

429
00:33:32,680 --> 00:33:35,200
Did you search them all?

430
00:33:35,280 --> 00:33:36,560
All done.

431
00:33:36,640 --> 00:33:37,920
Then take them inside.

432
00:33:38,680 --> 00:33:40,080
Hey, stay still. Get up.

433
00:33:41,080 --> 00:33:41,920
- Go.
- Hey.

434
00:33:42,560 --> 00:33:43,880
- Walk.
- Get up.

435
00:33:43,960 --> 00:33:45,000
Hey.

436
00:33:45,080 --> 00:33:47,720
- Hey, get up.
- Oh, what?

437
00:33:47,800 --> 00:33:49,720
- Get up.
- Easy, bro.

438
00:33:50,560 --> 00:33:52,360
- Get up!
- Yes.

439
00:33:52,440 --> 00:33:53,360
- Hey.
- Whoa.

440
00:33:54,440 --> 00:33:57,040
Hey, hey. Why are you going with them?

441
00:34:24,360 --> 00:34:25,360
Please.

442
00:34:54,880 --> 00:34:56,000
Praew?

443
00:34:56,080 --> 00:34:57,920
Long time no see, Sarge.

444
00:35:03,560 --> 00:35:05,040
Walk. Hurry up!

445
00:35:05,120 --> 00:35:06,920
- Go.
- Faster!

446
00:35:07,920 --> 00:35:09,520
- Hurry.
- Ow.

447
00:35:09,600 --> 00:35:11,520
- I know.
- Go over there. Go.

448
00:35:12,240 --> 00:35:14,200
- Don't be slow. You two sit there.
- Yes.

449
00:35:14,280 --> 00:35:15,760
- Come here.
- Go.

450
00:35:15,840 --> 00:35:17,600
I warned you. You didn't hit your target?

451
00:35:17,680 --> 00:35:19,280
Didn't hit your target?

452
00:35:19,360 --> 00:35:21,520
You didn't hit it?

453
00:35:21,600 --> 00:35:24,000
Get up and get back to work!

454
00:35:25,040 --> 00:35:26,720
- Damn it.
- Hey.

455
00:35:27,360 --> 00:35:29,480
Don't butt into other people's business.

456
00:35:29,560 --> 00:35:30,680
Work.

457
00:35:32,200 --> 00:35:35,640
Go. Sit down. Sit.

458
00:35:36,520 --> 00:35:37,680
What's wrong with him?

459
00:35:39,680 --> 00:35:41,440
Even if you're new,

460
00:35:41,520 --> 00:35:43,760
you still have to hit the same target.

461
00:35:43,840 --> 00:35:44,680
Got it?

462
00:35:46,960 --> 00:35:50,480
Bro, I'm not good at lying.

463
00:35:51,280 --> 00:35:52,120
Hey.

464
00:35:52,960 --> 00:35:54,800
If you're really scared of dying,

465
00:35:55,840 --> 00:35:57,240
you'll learn fast.

466
00:35:57,320 --> 00:35:58,440
Just do it.

467
00:35:59,440 --> 00:36:00,440
All right.

468
00:36:03,320 --> 00:36:05,120
Play along and let them lower their guard.

469
00:36:10,680 --> 00:36:11,600
Akki,

470
00:36:12,440 --> 00:36:14,120
this is just one room.

471
00:36:14,200 --> 00:36:16,720
I saw many more earlier.

472
00:36:16,800 --> 00:36:18,240
I think

473
00:36:18,320 --> 00:36:20,480
this place is their golden goose.

474
00:36:20,560 --> 00:36:22,520
It's their cash cow.

475
00:36:24,160 --> 00:36:25,400
Don't worry.

476
00:36:25,920 --> 00:36:28,400
I've got this. It's my specialty.

477
00:36:31,120 --> 00:36:32,240
Hey!

478
00:36:34,400 --> 00:36:36,920
Are you done chatting?

479
00:36:38,200 --> 00:36:39,560
If you don't work,

480
00:36:40,480 --> 00:36:41,760
I'll deal with you.

481
00:36:42,280 --> 00:36:44,600
How did you manage to step on the table?

482
00:36:45,880 --> 00:36:47,040
I'm a badass.

483
00:36:47,680 --> 00:36:48,680
Keep going.

484
00:37:28,040 --> 00:37:30,240
Auntie, please click

485
00:37:30,320 --> 00:37:33,680
the link I sent, fill in your info,

486
00:37:33,760 --> 00:37:36,240
and 200,000 <i>baht</i>
will be transferred to your account.

487
00:37:42,920 --> 00:37:45,280
Did you get in the system yet?

488
00:37:45,360 --> 00:37:48,680
Give me a sec.
They have multi-layer firewall.

489
00:37:48,760 --> 00:37:49,600
Hurry.

490
00:37:56,920 --> 00:37:59,200
Too late, Akki. Hurry up.

491
00:38:02,360 --> 00:38:04,120
What, Auntie?

492
00:38:04,200 --> 00:38:07,160
I told you I'm not a scammer.

493
00:38:07,240 --> 00:38:09,120
If you don't believe me,

494
00:38:09,200 --> 00:38:10,920
call the police.

495
00:38:11,000 --> 00:38:13,800
- I'll send the address. Come here.
- Hey.

496
00:38:14,720 --> 00:38:16,200
Why are you yelling?

497
00:38:17,040 --> 00:38:18,840
She doesn't believe us.

498
00:38:18,920 --> 00:38:21,080
She thinks we're scammers.

499
00:38:21,160 --> 00:38:23,280
It's been an hour.

500
00:38:23,360 --> 00:38:25,440
I still haven't closed.

501
00:38:25,520 --> 00:38:29,400
And she's super…

502
00:38:33,160 --> 00:38:34,280
annoying.

503
00:38:36,160 --> 00:38:38,240
Annoying, huh?

504
00:38:38,920 --> 00:38:41,160
I told you,

505
00:38:41,240 --> 00:38:42,800
- I can't lie.
- Hey, hey.

506
00:38:42,880 --> 00:38:44,880
Hey. What's your problem?

507
00:38:44,960 --> 00:38:48,560
Whoa. You causing trouble? Huh?

508
00:38:48,640 --> 00:38:50,520
- Huh? Come here.
- Ouch.

509
00:38:50,600 --> 00:38:53,400
You have a problem? You wanna fight?

510
00:39:03,240 --> 00:39:05,760
- All set?
- Bombs are planted.

511
00:39:05,840 --> 00:39:09,440
Nice. Take this.

512
00:39:09,520 --> 00:39:11,080
You always order me around.

513
00:39:11,160 --> 00:39:12,880
You're complaining now?

514
00:39:15,520 --> 00:39:19,120
Alright. Done. Huh?

515
00:39:24,480 --> 00:39:25,520
Hurry.

516
00:39:57,280 --> 00:40:01,040
I need to prove
whether you really are a spy.

517
00:40:14,320 --> 00:40:17,560
<i>We must deal with the Seven Legends.</i>
<i>Kill them all.</i>

518
00:40:20,040 --> 00:40:22,480
Then I'll start the hunt for Phoenix

519
00:40:23,320 --> 00:40:25,640
to get Ms. Duangnet back.

520
00:40:37,680 --> 00:40:40,840
Breathe. Calm down.

521
00:40:41,880 --> 00:40:44,320
- Say it calmly, "Sit."
- Sit.

522
00:40:44,400 --> 00:40:47,400
That's it. That's how women do it.

523
00:40:48,040 --> 00:40:50,480
- Stay quiet. Two, three, come in.
- Go.

524
00:40:50,560 --> 00:40:51,400
- Yes.
- Go.

525
00:41:02,720 --> 00:41:03,600
Wait and open the door.

526
00:41:03,680 --> 00:41:05,440
She walks past. Look far ahead.

527
00:41:05,520 --> 00:41:06,360
Look at her.

528
00:41:10,360 --> 00:41:13,280
- Whoa.
- Whoa.

529
00:41:13,360 --> 00:41:14,320
Someone's calling.

530
00:41:18,920 --> 00:41:21,800
Shit. Go talk over there, by the window.

531
00:41:22,640 --> 00:41:23,760
Oops.

532
00:41:23,840 --> 00:41:27,040
- Good. I like it. Go with this one.
- Yeah, go with it.

533
00:41:30,200 --> 00:41:33,040
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
